1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:05,085
On a tiny island you could drive across in an hour, an old man once taught children to play football on the sand.

2
00:00:05,135 --> 00:00:09,420
Tonight, those children are at the World Cup.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:12,890
And he is watching.

4
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:21,320
Last time, we predicted Australia and Turkey would trade blows and draw.

5
00:00:21,370 --> 00:00:26,190
Tonight — the oldest story in football. David... and the machine.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,660
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode twelve. Germany versus Curacao.

7
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:34,370
The giant... against the island.

8
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:43,540
And stay with me — because in the thirty-fourth minute, a man from a tiny island makes the save of the tournament.

9
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,795
First, the giant. Germany. Four World Cup titles.

10
00:00:49,845 --> 00:00:53,140
A conveyor belt of talent that simply never stops producing.

11
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:02,150
And now their most thrilling generation in decades — led by a boy they call Bambi.

12
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:15,970
Jamal Musiala, the Dribble King, whose slalom runs draw gasps from opponents and comparisons to Messi from everyone else.

13
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:23,415
Beside him, Florian Wirtz — a hundred million euros of vision, seeing passes from another dimension.

14
00:01:23,465 --> 00:01:28,380
Germany have not lost a World Cup opener this century.

15
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:33,390
But across the pitch stands a nation of a hundred and fifty thousand people.

16
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,850
Curacao.

17
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:43,750
An island you could drive across in an hour — at their first World Cup in history.

18
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:49,385
But do not pity them.

19
00:01:49,435 --> 00:01:54,320
Their players carry Dutch passports and Dutch football DNA — graduates of the same Ajax and Feyenoord academies that taught the world Total Football.

20
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,110
Small islands, they like to say, produce big hearts.

21
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:10,470
And in goal stands a man who has spent a career proving exactly that.

22
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,425
Eloy Room. The Columbus Crew legend.

23
00:02:17,475 --> 00:02:20,900
Six-foot-two of calm, carrying an entire island on his gloves.

24
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:27,540
Juninho Bacuna drives the midfield for every child who ever kicked a ball on a Caribbean beach.

25
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:31,630
Rangelo Janga reads danger like a book.

26
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:36,165
They are fearless, technical, and they cannot quite believe they are here.

27
00:02:36,215 --> 00:02:38,880
That makes them dangerous.

28
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,160
When the minnow stares into the eyes of the whale... and refuses to blink.

29
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:53,510
And the duel inside the match: Musiala against Room. The Dribble King...

30
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:57,570
against the island's wall. Magic against defiance.

31
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:03,835
Our prediction — built on four stars, on Total Football roots, and on one impossible save.

32
00:03:03,885 --> 00:03:07,220
Watch.

33
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,840
Thirty-fourth minute.

34
00:03:12,890 --> 00:03:17,230
Musiala glides past two — the ball breaks to Wirtz — he curls it for the top corner, surely a goal —

35
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:21,585
ROOM! He flies — and tips it over the bar!

36
00:03:21,635 --> 00:03:25,320
Three thousand Curacao fans erupt as if they have won the World Cup!

37
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,805
But the machine does not stop. Wave after wave. Musiala finishes.

38
00:03:30,855 --> 00:03:34,660
Wirtz adds a second. Havertz makes it three.

39
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:42,630
Germany are simply too much. The class of a giant, in full flow.

40
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,405
Three-nil at full time, in our story.

41
00:03:47,455 --> 00:03:49,860
But the night does not belong to the scoreline.

42
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:57,195
It belongs to Eloy Room — who reminded a giant that the fight was real.

43
00:03:57,245 --> 00:04:01,440
Some teams lose the match... and still win the day.

44
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,715
Do you agree? Comment MACHINE if Germany go all the way this summer.

45
00:04:06,765 --> 00:04:09,980
Comment DAVID if Curacao's pride steals your heart.

46
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:16,015
And the old man on the sand? Legend number twelve: the Beach Keeper.

47
00:04:16,065 --> 00:04:19,580
He taught the island to dream with a ball at its feet.

48
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:31,130
Tonight, his children stood toe to toe with a giant. Collect him inside the game.

49
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,377
Which brings us to YOU.

50
00:04:35,427 --> 00:04:38,303
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

51
00:04:38,353 --> 00:04:41,230
scores for you.

52
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:49,730
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple — like Curacao tonight.

53
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,675
Hit like — send this to the friend who always roots for the little guy.

54
00:04:53,725 --> 00:04:57,200
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

